Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Boil a full #kettle{}. Sandwich each @skin-on British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated). Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}.

Pour the @water for the stock{450%ml}(boiling) into a #measuring jug{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat (if you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal saucepan and transfer to an ovenproof dish later). Once the pan is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir-fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the leek and mushrooms, then stir-fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g} to the pan. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add half the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, stir together and allow the vinegar to evaporate, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the boiled water and @chicken stock paste{15%g}, then stir well to combine. Bring to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While the risotto bakes, halve the @premium tomato mix{125%g}. Pour the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and remaining cider vinegar into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}. Mix together, then set the dressing aside. Just before you are ready to serve, pop the @wild rocket{40%g} and tomatoes into the dressing bowl and toss to coat.

Once the risotto has baked for ~{10%minutes}, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden-brown, ~{5-6%minutes} each side. Transfer the cooked chicken to a #plate{} to rest for a couple of minutes, loosely covered in foil.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @butter{20%g} and three quarters of the @Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it needs loosening.

Spoon the risotto into #bowls{}, then slice the chicken widthways into 5 pieces and lay on top. Finish your ultimate chicken, bacon and mushroom risotto with a sprinkle of the remaining parmesan and serve the salad alongside. Enjoy!